{
  "video_id": "hItQZfVU6-g",
  "title": "How we can design timeless cities for our collective future | Vishaan Chakrabarti",
  "es": 1,
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 13603.0,
      "end_time": 14793.0,
      "text": "Travel with me"
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 14817.0,
      "end_time": 18681.0,
      "text": "to some of the most beautiful spots in cities around the world:"
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 19452.0,
      "end_time": 21720.0,
      "text": "Rome&#39;s Spanish steps;"
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 21744.0,
      "end_time": 26655.0,
      "text": "the historic neighborhoods of Paris and Shanghai;"
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 28600.0,
      "end_time": 30530.0,
      "text": "the rolling landscape of Central Park;"
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 31430.0,
      "end_time": 36134.0,
      "text": "the tight-knit blocks of Tokyo or Fez;"
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 37509.0,
      "end_time": 41487.0,
      "text": "the wildly sloping streets of the favelas of Rio de Janeiro;"
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 42960.0,
      "end_time": 45863.0,
      "text": "the dizzying step wells of Jaipur;"
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 48127.0,
      "end_time": 50895.0,
      "text": "the arched pedestrian bridges of Venice."
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 53165.0,
      "end_time": 55498.0,
      "text": "Now let&#39;s go to some newer cities."
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 56930.0,
      "end_time": 60970.0,
      "text": "Six downtowns built across six continents in the 20th century."
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 61763.0,
      "end_time": 66717.0,
      "text": "Why do none of these places have any of the charming characteristics"
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 66741.0,
      "end_time": 68152.0,
      "text": "of our older cities?"
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 69700.0,
      "end_time": 75980.0,
      "text": "Or let&#39;s go to six suburbs built on six continents in the 20th century."
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 76540.0,
      "end_time": 81197.0,
      "text": "Why do none of them have any of the lyrical qualities"
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 81221.0,
      "end_time": 85204.0,
      "text": "that we associate with the places that we cherish the most?"
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 87196.0,
      "end_time": 90617.0,
      "text": "Now, maybe you think I&#39;m just being nostalgic --"
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 90641.0,
      "end_time": 91805.0,
      "text": "why does it matter?"
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 91829.0,
      "end_time": 96470.0,
      "text": "Who cares if there is this creeping sameness besetting our planet?"
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 97442.0,
      "end_time": 102612.0,
      "text": "Well, it matters because most people around the world"
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 102636.0,
      "end_time": 105402.0,
      "text": "are gravitating to urban areas globally."
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 106434.0,
      "end_time": 110561.0,
      "text": "And how we design those urban areas could well determine"
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 110585.0,
      "end_time": 113830.0,
      "text": "whether we thrive or not as a species."
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 113934.0,
      "end_time": 120515.0,
      "text": "So, we already know that people who live in transit-rich areas,"
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 120540.0,
      "end_time": 122121.0,
      "text": "live in apartment buildings,"
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 122145.0,
      "end_time": 124957.0,
      "text": "have a far lower carbon footprint"
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 124981.0,
      "end_time": 126940.0,
      "text": "than their suburban counterparts."
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 127276.0,
      "end_time": 130410.0,
      "text": "So maybe one lesson from that is if you love nature,"
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 130434.0,
      "end_time": 131683.0,
      "text": "you shouldn&#39;t live in it."
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 131707.0,
      "end_time": 134120.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 135157.0,
      "end_time": 137307.0,
      "text": "But I think the dry statistics"
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 137331.0,
      "end_time": 139600.0,
      "text": "of what&#39;s known as transit-oriented development"
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 139624.0,
      "end_time": 141363.0,
      "text": "only tells part of the story."
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 142339.0,
      "end_time": 146585.0,
      "text": "Because cities, if they&#39;re going to attract people,"
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 146609.0,
      "end_time": 147853.0,
      "text": "have to be great."
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 148306.0,
      "end_time": 152617.0,
      "text": "They have to be powerful magnets with distinctive appeal"
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 152641.0,
      "end_time": 155600.0,
      "text": "to bring in all those new green urbanites."
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 156125.0,
      "end_time": 159299.0,
      "text": "And this is not just an aesthetic issue, mind you."
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 159323.0,
      "end_time": 162608.0,
      "text": "This is an issue of international consequence."
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 163419.0,
      "end_time": 166958.0,
      "text": "Because today, every day,"
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 166982.0,
      "end_time": 173379.0,
      "text": "literally hundreds of thousands of people are moving into a city somewhere,"
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 173403.0,
      "end_time": 175203.0,
      "text": "mainly in the Global South."
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 176641.0,
      "end_time": 179664.0,
      "text": "And when you think about that, ask yourself:"
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 179688.0,
      "end_time": 182315.0,
      "text": "Are they condemned to live in the same bland cities"
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 182339.0,
      "end_time": 184387.0,
      "text": "we built in the 20th century,"
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 184411.0,
      "end_time": 186683.0,
      "text": "or can we offer them something better?"
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 187736.0,
      "end_time": 189101.0,
      "text": "And to answer that question,"
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 189125.0,
      "end_time": 192409.0,
      "text": "you have to unpack how we got here in the first place."
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 193287.0,
      "end_time": 195365.0,
      "text": "First: mass production."
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 195857.0,
      "end_time": 199310.0,
      "text": "Just like consumer goods and chain stores,"
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 199334.0,
      "end_time": 204887.0,
      "text": "we mass-produce glass and steel and concrete and asphalt and drywall,"
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 204911.0,
      "end_time": 209243.0,
      "text": "and we deploy them in mind-numbingly similar ways across the planet."
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 211165.0,
      "end_time": 213465.0,
      "text": "Second: regulation."
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 213934.0,
      "end_time": 216196.0,
      "text": "So, take cars, for instance."
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 216561.0,
      "end_time": 219204.0,
      "text": "Cars travel at very high speeds."
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 219228.0,
      "end_time": 221164.0,
      "text": "They&#39;re susceptible to human error."
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 221188.0,
      "end_time": 224792.0,
      "text": "So when we&#39;re asked, as architects, to design a new street,"
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 224816.0,
      "end_time": 226668.0,
      "text": "we have to look at drawings like this,"
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 226692.0,
      "end_time": 228768.0,
      "text": "that tell us how high a curb needs to be,"
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 228792.0,
      "end_time": 231926.0,
      "text": "that pedestrians need to be over here and vehicles over there,"
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 231950.0,
      "end_time": 234798.0,
      "text": "a loading zone here, a drop-off there."
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 234823.0,
      "end_time": 237561.0,
      "text": "What the car really did in the 20th century"
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 237585.0,
      "end_time": 241520.0,
      "text": "is it created this carved-up, segregated landscape."
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 243330.0,
      "end_time": 246861.0,
      "text": "Or take the ladder fire truck -- you know, those big ladder trucks"
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 246885.0,
      "end_time": 249582.0,
      "text": "that are used to rescue people from burning buildings?"
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 251776.0,
      "end_time": 254850.0,
      "text": "Those have such a wide turning radius,"
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 254109.0,
      "end_time": 258942.0,
      "text": "that we have to deploy an enormous amount of pavement, of asphalt,"
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 258966.0,
      "end_time": 260233.0,
      "text": "to accommodate them."
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 262633.0,
      "end_time": 265633.0,
      "text": "Or take the critically important wheelchair."
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 265990.0,
      "end_time": 270172.0,
      "text": "A wheelchair necessitates a landscape of minimal slopes"
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 270196.0,
      "end_time": 271887.0,
      "text": "and redundant vertical circulation."
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 271911.0,
      "end_time": 275148.0,
      "text": "So wherever there&#39;s a stair, there has to be an elevator or a ramp."
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 276323.0,
      "end_time": 280697.0,
      "text": "Now, don&#39;t get me wrong, please -- I am all for pedestrian safety,"
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 280721.0,
      "end_time": 282215.0,
      "text": "firefighting"
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 282239.0,
      "end_time": 283847.0,
      "text": "and certainly, wheelchair access."
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 283872.0,
      "end_time": 286943.0,
      "text": "Both of my parents were in wheelchairs at the end of their lives,"
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 286967.0,
      "end_time": 288942.0,
      "text": "so I understand very much that struggle."
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 289419.0,
      "end_time": 293637.0,
      "text": "But we also have to acknowledge that all of these well-intentioned rules,"
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 294608.0,
      "end_time": 297926.0,
      "text": "they had the tremendous unintended consequence"
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 297950.0,
      "end_time": 302587.0,
      "text": "of making illegal the ways in which we used to build cities."
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 305191.0,
      "end_time": 308364.0,
      "text": "Similarly illegal: at the end of the 19th century,"
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 308388.0,
      "end_time": 310207.0,
      "text": "right after the elevator was invented,"
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 310231.0,
      "end_time": 313379.0,
      "text": "we built these charming urban buildings,"
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 313403.0,
      "end_time": 315593.0,
      "text": "these lovely buildings, all over the world,"
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 315617.0,
      "end_time": 316990.0,
      "text": "from Italy to India."
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 317752.0,
      "end_time": 320537.0,
      "text": "And they had maybe 10 or 12 apartments in them."
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 320561.0,
      "end_time": 324243.0,
      "text": "They had one small elevator and a staircase that wrapped them"
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 324267.0,
      "end_time": 325417.0,
      "text": "and a light well."
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 325903.0,
      "end_time": 329975.0,
      "text": "And not only were they charming buildings that were cost-effective,"
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 329999.0,
      "end_time": 331196.0,
      "text": "they were communal --"
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 331220.0,
      "end_time": 334420.0,
      "text": "you ran into your neighbor on that stairwell."
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 335530.0,
      "end_time": 336820.0,
      "text": "Well, you can&#39;t build this, either."
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 337506.0,
      "end_time": 341688.0,
      "text": "By contrast, today, when we have to build a major new apartment building somewhere,"
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 341712.0,
      "end_time": 343942.0,
      "text": "we have to build lots and lots of elevators"
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 343966.0,
      "end_time": 345871.0,
      "text": "and lots of fire stairs,"
    },
    {
      "index": 96,
      "start_time": 345895.0,
      "end_time": 351361.0,
      "text": "and we have to connect them with these long, anonymous, dreary corridors."
    },
    {
      "index": 97,
      "start_time": 352524.0,
      "end_time": 355944.0,
      "text": "Now, developers -- when they&#39;re confronted with the cost"
    },
    {
      "index": 98,
      "start_time": 355968.0,
      "end_time": 358302.0,
      "text": "of all of that common infrastructure,"
    },
    {
      "index": 99,
      "start_time": 358326.0,
      "end_time": 361443.0,
      "text": "they have to spread that cost over more apartments,"
    },
    {
      "index": 100,
      "start_time": 361467.0,
      "end_time": 363671.0,
      "text": "so they want to build bigger buildings."
    },
    {
      "index": 101,
      "start_time": 364220.0,
      "end_time": 368387.0,
      "text": "What that results in is the thud,"
    },
    {
      "index": 102,
      "start_time": 368411.0,
      "end_time": 373490.0,
      "text": "the dull thud of the same apartment building being built"
    },
    {
      "index": 103,
      "start_time": 373514.0,
      "end_time": 376156.0,
      "text": "in every city across the world."
    },
    {
      "index": 104,
      "start_time": 377166.0,
      "end_time": 380332.0,
      "text": "And this is not only creating physical sameness,"
    },
    {
      "index": 105,
      "start_time": 380357.0,
      "end_time": 382626.0,
      "text": "it&#39;s creating social sameness,"
    },
    {
      "index": 106,
      "start_time": 382650.0,
      "end_time": 385760.0,
      "text": "because these buildings are more expensive to build,"
    },
    {
      "index": 107,
      "start_time": 385784.0,
      "end_time": 388418.0,
      "text": "and it helped to create an affordability crisis"
    },
    {
      "index": 108,
      "start_time": 388442.0,
      "end_time": 392573.0,
      "text": "in cities all over the world, including places like Vancouver."
    },
    {
      "index": 109,
      "start_time": 393688.0,
      "end_time": 396625.0,
      "text": "Now, I said there was a third reason for all this sameness,"
    },
    {
      "index": 110,
      "start_time": 396649.0,
      "end_time": 398790.0,
      "text": "and that&#39;s really a psychological one."
    },
    {
      "index": 111,
      "start_time": 399220.0,
      "end_time": 400863.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s a fear of difference,"
    },
    {
      "index": 112,
      "start_time": 400887.0,
      "end_time": 403687.0,
      "text": "and architects hear this all the time from their clients:"
    },
    {
      "index": 113,
      "start_time": 403711.0,
      "end_time": 407413.0,
      "text": "\"If I try that new idea, will I be sued?"
    },
    {
      "index": 114,
      "start_time": 408165.0,
      "end_time": 409418.0,
      "text": "Will I be mocked?"
    },
    {
      "index": 115,
      "start_time": 410546.0,
      "end_time": 412545.0,
      "text": "Better safe than sorry.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 116,
      "start_time": 413450.0,
      "end_time": 416974.0,
      "text": "And all of these things have conspired together"
    },
    {
      "index": 117,
      "start_time": 416998.0,
      "end_time": 422897.0,
      "text": "to blanket our planet with a homogeneity that I think is deeply problematic."
    },
    {
      "index": 118,
      "start_time": 423660.0,
      "end_time": 425525.0,
      "text": "So how can we do the opposite?"
    },
    {
      "index": 119,
      "start_time": 425549.0,
      "end_time": 427794.0,
      "text": "How can we go back to building cities"
    },
    {
      "index": 120,
      "start_time": 427819.0,
      "end_time": 431545.0,
      "text": "that are physically and culturally varied again?"
    },
    {
      "index": 121,
      "start_time": 431569.0,
      "end_time": 434103.0,
      "text": "How can we build cities of difference?"
    },
    {
      "index": 122,
      "start_time": 434823.0,
      "end_time": 437133.0,
      "text": "I would argue that we should start"
    },
    {
      "index": 123,
      "start_time": 437157.0,
      "end_time": 440366.0,
      "text": "by injecting into the global the local."
    },
    {
      "index": 124,
      "start_time": 440814.0,
      "end_time": 443742.0,
      "text": "This is already happening with food, for instance."
    },
    {
      "index": 125,
      "start_time": 444760.0,
      "end_time": 449315.0,
      "text": "You just look at the way in which craft beer has taken on corporate beer."
    },
    {
      "index": 126,
      "start_time": 450704.0,
      "end_time": 454101.0,
      "text": "Or, how many of you still eat Wonder Bread?"
    },
    {
      "index": 127,
      "start_time": 455164.0,
      "end_time": 457171.0,
      "text": "I&#39;d bet most of you don&#39;t."
    },
    {
      "index": 128,
      "start_time": 457196.0,
      "end_time": 459929.0,
      "text": "And I bet you don&#39;t because you don&#39;t want processed food"
    },
    {
      "index": 129,
      "start_time": 459953.0,
      "end_time": 461126.0,
      "text": "in your life."
    },
    {
      "index": 130,
      "start_time": 461151.0,
      "end_time": 463930.0,
      "text": "So if you don&#39;t want processed food,"
    },
    {
      "index": 131,
      "start_time": 463117.0,
      "end_time": 465760.0,
      "text": "why would you want processed cities?"
    },
    {
      "index": 132,
      "start_time": 465784.0,
      "end_time": 468903.0,
      "text": "Why would you want these mass-produced, bleached places"
    },
    {
      "index": 133,
      "start_time": 468927.0,
      "end_time": 471715.0,
      "text": "where all of us have to live and work every day?"
    },
    {
      "index": 134,
      "start_time": 473498.0,
      "end_time": 478920.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    },
    {
      "index": 135,
      "start_time": 478806.0,
      "end_time": 483503.0,
      "text": "So, technology was a big part of the problem in the 20th century."
    },
    {
      "index": 136,
      "start_time": 483528.0,
      "end_time": 486770.0,
      "text": "When we invented the automobile, what happened is,"
    },
    {
      "index": 137,
      "start_time": 486101.0,
      "end_time": 488834.0,
      "text": "the world all bent towards the invention."
    },
    {
      "index": 138,
      "start_time": 489363.0,
      "end_time": 491751.0,
      "text": "And we recreated our landscape around it."
    },
    {
      "index": 139,
      "start_time": 492125.0,
      "end_time": 494625.0,
      "text": "In the 21st century,"
    },
    {
      "index": 140,
      "start_time": 494649.0,
      "end_time": 497410.0,
      "text": "technology can be part of the solution --"
    },
    {
      "index": 141,
      "start_time": 497434.0,
      "end_time": 500259.0,
      "text": "if it bends to the needs of the world."
    },
    {
      "index": 142,
      "start_time": 501730.0,
      "end_time": 503140.0,
      "text": "So what do I mean by that?"
    },
    {
      "index": 143,
      "start_time": 503380.0,
      "end_time": 504423.0,
      "text": "Take the autonomous vehicle."
    },
    {
      "index": 144,
      "start_time": 504447.0,
      "end_time": 508193.0,
      "text": "I don&#39;t think the autonomous vehicle is exciting because it&#39;s a driverless car."
    },
    {
      "index": 145,
      "start_time": 508217.0,
      "end_time": 509830.0,
      "text": "That, to me, only implies"
    },
    {
      "index": 146,
      "start_time": 509855.0,
      "end_time": 513251.0,
      "text": "that there&#39;s even more congestion on the roads, frankly."
    },
    {
      "index": 147,
      "start_time": 514130.0,
      "end_time": 517872.0,
      "text": "I think what&#39;s exciting about the autonomous vehicle is the promise --"
    },
    {
      "index": 148,
      "start_time": 517895.0,
      "end_time": 519853.0,
      "text": "and I want to stress the word \"promise,\""
    },
    {
      "index": 149,
      "start_time": 519878.00000000006,
      "end_time": 521848.00000000006,
      "text": "given the recent accident in Arizona --"
    },
    {
      "index": 150,
      "start_time": 522577.0,
      "end_time": 525886.0,
      "text": "the promise that we could have these small, urban vehicles"
    },
    {
      "index": 151,
      "start_time": 525910.0,
      "end_time": 530246.0,
      "text": "that could safely comingle with pedestrians and bicycles."
    },
    {
      "index": 152,
      "start_time": 530776.0,
      "end_time": 534712.0,
      "text": "That would enable us to design humane streets again,"
    },
    {
      "index": 153,
      "start_time": 534736.0,
      "end_time": 536348.0,
      "text": "streets without curbs,"
    },
    {
      "index": 154,
      "start_time": 536372.0,
      "end_time": 539497.0,
      "text": "maybe streets like the wooden walkways on Fire Island."
    },
    {
      "index": 155,
      "start_time": 541780.0,
      "end_time": 546174.0,
      "text": "Or maybe we could design streets with the cobblestone of the 21st century,"
    },
    {
      "index": 156,
      "start_time": 546198.0,
      "end_time": 549667.0,
      "text": "something that captures kinetic energy, melts snow,"
    },
    {
      "index": 157,
      "start_time": 549691.0,
      "end_time": 552103.0,
      "text": "helps you with your fitness when you walk."
    },
    {
      "index": 158,
      "start_time": 553720.0,
      "end_time": 556268.0,
      "text": "Or remember those big ladder fire trucks?"
    },
    {
      "index": 159,
      "start_time": 556292.0,
      "end_time": 560164.0,
      "text": "What if we could replace them and all the asphalt that comes with them"
    },
    {
      "index": 160,
      "start_time": 560188.0,
      "end_time": 564188.0,
      "text": "with drones and robots that could rescue people from burning buildings?"
    },
    {
      "index": 161,
      "start_time": 564212.0,
      "end_time": 566997.0,
      "text": "And if you think that&#39;s outlandish, you&#39;d be amazed to know"
    },
    {
      "index": 162,
      "start_time": 567220.0,
      "end_time": 570466.0,
      "text": "how much of that technology is already being used today"
    },
    {
      "index": 163,
      "start_time": 570490.0,
      "end_time": 571757.0,
      "text": "in rescue activity."
    },
    {
      "index": 164,
      "start_time": 573291.0,
      "end_time": 576370.0,
      "text": "But now I&#39;d like you to really imagine with me."
    },
    {
      "index": 165,
      "start_time": 576966.0,
      "end_time": 581154.0,
      "text": "Imagine if we could design the hovercraft wheelchair."
    },
    {
      "index": 166,
      "start_time": 582299.0,
      "end_time": 583464.0,
      "text": "Right?"
    },
    {
      "index": 167,
      "start_time": 583488.0,
      "end_time": 587228.0,
      "text": "An invention that would not only allow equal access,"
    },
    {
      "index": 168,
      "start_time": 587252.0,
      "end_time": 592766.0,
      "text": "but would enable us to build the Italian hill town of the 21st century."
    },
    {
      "index": 169,
      "start_time": 594244.0,
      "end_time": 596545.0,
      "text": "I think you&#39;d be amazed to know"
    },
    {
      "index": 170,
      "start_time": 596569.0,
      "end_time": 601356.0,
      "text": "that just a few of these inventions, responsive to human need,"
    },
    {
      "index": 171,
      "start_time": 601380.0,
      "end_time": 605830.0,
      "text": "would completely transform the way we could build our cities."
    },
    {
      "index": 172,
      "start_time": 606253.0,
      "end_time": 608328.0,
      "text": "Now, I bet you&#39;re also thinking:"
    },
    {
      "index": 173,
      "start_time": 608352.0,
      "end_time": 612450.0,
      "text": "\"We don&#39;t have kinetic cobblestones or flying wheelchairs yet,"
    },
    {
      "index": 174,
      "start_time": 612690.0,
      "end_time": 615466.0,
      "text": "so what can we do about this problem with today&#39;s technology?\""
    },
    {
      "index": 175,
      "start_time": 615990.0,
      "end_time": 620712.0,
      "text": "And my inspiration for that question comes from a very different city,"
    },
    {
      "index": 176,
      "start_time": 620736.0,
      "end_time": 623770.0,
      "text": "the city of Ulaanbaatar, Mongolia."
    },
    {
      "index": 177,
      "start_time": 623101.0,
      "end_time": 624264.0,
      "text": "I have clients there"
    },
    {
      "index": 178,
      "start_time": 624288.0,
      "end_time": 628942.0,
      "text": "who have asked us to design a 21st-century open-air village"
    },
    {
      "index": 179,
      "start_time": 628966.0,
      "end_time": 633244.0,
      "text": "that&#39;s sustainably heated using today&#39;s technology,"
    },
    {
      "index": 180,
      "start_time": 633268.0,
      "end_time": 635474.0,
      "text": "in the heart of their downtown."
    },
    {
      "index": 181,
      "start_time": 635498.0,
      "end_time": 638165.0,
      "text": "And that&#39;s to cope with their frigid winters."
    },
    {
      "index": 182,
      "start_time": 638918.0,
      "end_time": 642180.0,
      "text": "And the project is both poetry and prose."
    },
    {
      "index": 183,
      "start_time": 642204.0,
      "end_time": 646600.0,
      "text": "The poetry is really about evoking the local:"
    },
    {
      "index": 184,
      "start_time": 646850.0,
      "end_time": 647888.0,
      "text": "the mountainous terrain,"
    },
    {
      "index": 185,
      "start_time": 647912.0,
      "end_time": 651490.0,
      "text": "using colors to pick up the spectacular light,"
    },
    {
      "index": 186,
      "start_time": 651514.0,
      "end_time": 655366.0,
      "text": "understanding how to interpret the nomadic traditions"
    },
    {
      "index": 187,
      "start_time": 655390.0,
      "end_time": 657964.0,
      "text": "that animate the nation of Mongolia."
    },
    {
      "index": 188,
      "start_time": 659427.0,
      "end_time": 663180.0,
      "text": "The prose has been the development of a catalogue of buildings,"
    },
    {
      "index": 189,
      "start_time": 663204.0,
      "end_time": 666930.0,
      "text": "of small buildings that are fairly affordable,"
    },
    {
      "index": 190,
      "start_time": 666117.0,
      "end_time": 669195.0,
      "text": "using local construction materials and technology"
    },
    {
      "index": 191,
      "start_time": 669220.0,
      "end_time": 672450.0,
      "text": "that can still provide new forms of housing,"
    },
    {
      "index": 192,
      "start_time": 672690.0,
      "end_time": 673770.0,
      "text": "new workspace,"
    },
    {
      "index": 193,
      "start_time": 673794.0,
      "end_time": 674949.0,
      "text": "new shops"
    },
    {
      "index": 194,
      "start_time": 674973.0,
      "end_time": 677477.0,
      "text": "and cultural buildings, like a theater or a museum --"
    },
    {
      "index": 195,
      "start_time": 677501.0,
      "end_time": 678755.0,
      "text": "even a haunted house."
    },
    {
      "index": 196,
      "start_time": 681160.0,
      "end_time": 682814.0,
      "text": "While working on this in our office,"
    },
    {
      "index": 197,
      "start_time": 682838.0,
      "end_time": 686882.0,
      "text": "we&#39;ve realized that we&#39;re building upon the work of our colleagues,"
    },
    {
      "index": 198,
      "start_time": 686907.0,
      "end_time": 691191.0,
      "text": "including architect Tatiana Bilbao, working in Mexico City;"
    },
    {
      "index": 199,
      "start_time": 692220.0,
      "end_time": 696450.0,
      "text": "Pritzker laureate Alejandro Aravena, working in Chile;"
    },
    {
      "index": 200,
      "start_time": 696474.0,
      "end_time": 700189.0,
      "text": "and recent Pritzker winner Balkrishna Doshi, working in India."
    },
    {
      "index": 201,
      "start_time": 700506.0,
      "end_time": 705290.0,
      "text": "And all of them are building spectacular new forms of affordable housing,"
    },
    {
      "index": 202,
      "start_time": 705315.0,
      "end_time": 707815.0,
      "text": "but they&#39;re also building cities of difference,"
    },
    {
      "index": 203,
      "start_time": 707839.0,
      "end_time": 711910.0,
      "text": "because they&#39;re building cities that respond to local communities,"
    },
    {
      "index": 204,
      "start_time": 711934.0,
      "end_time": 713612.0,
      "text": "local climates"
    },
    {
      "index": 205,
      "start_time": 713636.0,
      "end_time": 715569.0,
      "text": "and local construction methods."
    },
    {
      "index": 206,
      "start_time": 717369.0,
      "end_time": 721334.0,
      "text": "We&#39;re doubling down on that idea, we&#39;re researching a new model"
    },
    {
      "index": 207,
      "start_time": 721358.0,
      "end_time": 725160.0,
      "text": "for our growing cities with gentrification pressures,"
    },
    {
      "index": 208,
      "start_time": 725184.0,
      "end_time": 727910.0,
      "text": "that could build upon that late-19th-century model"
    },
    {
      "index": 209,
      "start_time": 727934.0,
      "end_time": 729410.0,
      "text": "with that center core,"
    },
    {
      "index": 210,
      "start_time": 729434.0,
      "end_time": 735129.0,
      "text": "but a prototype that could shape-shift in response to local needs"
    },
    {
      "index": 211,
      "start_time": 735153.0,
      "end_time": 737319.0,
      "text": "and local building materials."
    },
    {
      "index": 212,
      "start_time": 738906.0,
      "end_time": 742748.0,
      "text": "All of these ideas, to me, are nostalgia-free."
    },
    {
      "index": 213,
      "start_time": 743276.0,
      "end_time": 745282.0,
      "text": "They all tell me"
    },
    {
      "index": 214,
      "start_time": 745307.0,
      "end_time": 748252.0,
      "text": "that we can build cities that can grow,"
    },
    {
      "index": 215,
      "start_time": 748276.0,
      "end_time": 751140.0,
      "text": "but grow in a way that reflects the diverse residents"
    },
    {
      "index": 216,
      "start_time": 751380.0,
      "end_time": 752569.0,
      "text": "that live in those cities;"
    },
    {
      "index": 217,
      "start_time": 753395.0,
      "end_time": 758355.0,
      "text": "grow in a way that can accommodate all income groups,"
    },
    {
      "index": 218,
      "start_time": 758379.0,
      "end_time": 760546.0,
      "text": "all colors, creeds, genders."
    },
    {
      "index": 219,
      "start_time": 762220.0,
      "end_time": 766501.0,
      "text": "We could build such spectacular cities that we could disincentivize sprawl"
    },
    {
      "index": 220,
      "start_time": 767304.0,
      "end_time": 769293.0,
      "text": "and actually protect nature."
    },
    {
      "index": 221,
      "start_time": 771260.0,
      "end_time": 773810.0,
      "text": "We can grow cities that are high-tech,"
    },
    {
      "index": 222,
      "start_time": 773834.0,
      "end_time": 778448.0,
      "text": "but also respond to the timeless cultural needs of the human spirit."
    },
    {
      "index": 223,
      "start_time": 779778.0,
      "end_time": 783214.0,
      "text": "I&#39;m convinced that we can build cities of difference"
    },
    {
      "index": 224,
      "start_time": 783238.0,
      "end_time": 787384.0,
      "text": "that help to create the global mosaic to which so many of us aspire."
    },
    {
      "index": 225,
      "start_time": 787786.0,
      "end_time": 788935.0,
      "text": "Thank you."
    },
    {
      "index": 226,
      "start_time": 788960.0,
      "end_time": 792603.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    }
  ]
}